\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Data taken over time or space are likely to be structured by physical and
 biological processes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our deterministic model may account for this structure.
 However, if the 
\emph on
residuals
\emph default
 show correlation over time and/ or space, then we are obliged to model
 their covariance to assure that iid assumptions are met.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Doing so requires estimating only a few more parameters, in most cases one
 or two, relative to the aspatial model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Fitting spatial models is computationally challenging.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Deciding whether to use a spatial or aspatial model should probably be treated
 as a problem in model selection.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
